{"type":"message","id":"6d374cab","parentId":"c610012a","timestamp":"2026-03-27T04:34:50.772Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Great! Aircrack is running and showing progress. It's testing keys at about 27k keys/sec, 0.32% complete, estimated time left ~6 minutes. The password hasn't been found yet. I should let it continue in background and monitor completion. Use `exec` with `background: true` and `pty: true` to run it in background, then poll with `process`. But the command already started in the foreground and produced output. I can kill it and restart in background. Let's start a new process with `exec` with `background: true`. Use the same command but maybe redirect output to a log file. Use `timeout` maybe 400 seconds (approx 7 minutes). Let's do:\n\n`echo '666' | sudo -S aircrack-ng -b D8:F6:07:DA:C0:E0 -w /tmp/rockyou.txt /tmp/wpa_capture-01.cap > /tmp/aircrack.log 2>&1`\n\nBut aircrack uses terminal escape sequences; redirecting might mess up. Better to let it run in PTY and capture output via process logs. Use `exec` with `pty: true`, `background: true`, and maybe `yieldMs: 10000`. Then use `process` to poll logs.\n\nLet's start. First, kill any existing aircrack processes. Use `pkill`. Let's do that.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_s0PYGHDvqViVciphdV4uLdWN","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo '666' | sudo -S pkill aircrack-ng 2>/dev/null; sleep 2; pgrep -x aircrack-ng || echo \"No aircrack running\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":3475,"output":687,"cacheRead":22208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26370,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774586077467,"responseId":"facb8281-8c57-4b02-94d1-e55f78c6b6e3"}}
