{"type":"message","id":"4a23033a","parentId":"ead2da35","timestamp":"2026-03-27T04:43:43.168Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No airodump running. Good. Now we need to set wlan1 to monitor mode. Use airmon-ng start wlan1. But we must be careful not to interfere with wlan0. Let's check if wlan1 is currently in use. Use iwconfig wlan1 maybe. Let's try. Use sudo iw dev wlan1 info. Already we saw it's managed. Let's bring it down, set monitor mode. We'll use airmon-ng check kill to kill interfering processes. That might kill network manager on wlan1 only? Should be okay. We'll do it stepwise. First, check if there are any interfering processes with airmon-ng check. Let's run airmon-ng check wlan1. Use sudo. Let's do it.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_V45lgPjKjAsDG413K9b4UMH6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"echo '666' | sudo -S airmon-ng check wlan1 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-reasoner","usage":{"input":262,"output":400,"cacheRead":46656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47318,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774586614867,"responseId":"ca089ac1-f85b-4954-8154-e754f6988d85"}}
